    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 score makes him the premier play on the board. Facing Landen Roupp, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and a favorable platoon advantage, solidifying his role as the anchor of the offense. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** (78.89) is in a prime spot against Kumar Rocker; the combination of a wind-out environment and a high-leverage batting position suggests he could be the primary catalyst for our Roto categories today. **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) also grades out as a top-tier start, as he faces Tomoyuki Sugano in a matchup where his elite SP skill projection significantly elevates his efficiency relative to the rest of the roster.\n\nWhile the core is strong, we are managing several marginal spots. **Josh Lowe** (48.80) and **Coby Mayo** (52.77) are our most volatile starters; **Josh Lowe** is battling a difficult matchup against Chase Burns, while **Coby Mayo** is being held back by a low spot in the order. The most difficult bench decision involved **Miguel Vargas** (51.34), who nearly cracked the lineup over **Marcell Ozuna** (54.50). Ultimately, the optimizer favored **Marcell Ozuna**'s raw base projection and park advantage despite a minor wind-in risk, while **Miguel Vargas** was sidelined due to lingering lineup uncertainty and a slightly lower overall scoring floor. \n\nRisk management remains a priority today, as every player except **Marcell Ozuna** is currently listed with a \"Lineup Pending\" status, forcing us to lean on historical order assumptions. We are also keeping a close eye on the stolen base potential provided by **Heliot Ramos** and **Andy Pages**, both of whom are projected to benefit from the slow delivery speeds of Shane Baz and Kumar Rocker, respectively. We will need to remain agile; should any of these players move down the order, we may need to reconsider the viability of lower-scoring assets like **Josh Lowe** or **Coby Mayo** to protect our daily game caps.",
